TYPES OF FILES:
================
- : regular files
b : blocked files
c : character files
d : directories
l : linked files

CREATE FILES
==================

touch filel            : to craete a file
touch file{1..10)      : to create multiple files
1s/11                  : to list files
cat filel              : to show the content in file
more filel             : to show the content in file
cat››file1             : to insert content
enter ctrl d           : to save and exit

COPY FILE AND RENAME:
==========================
cp filel file2         : copies content form filel to file2
cp -rp filel file2     : copies content form filel(source file) to file2 (destination file)
cat filel ›› file2     : copies content form filel to file2 losing data 
mv file1 file2         : to cut file1 and pastes file2
mv filel file2         : to rename file1(old name) with file2(new name)

REMOVE FILES:
=======================
rm file1               : to remove a file
rm file2 -f rm         : to remove a file forcefully
rm * ⁠-f                : to remove all files forcefully


head file1             : to print top 10 lines
head -5 file1          : to print top 5 lines
head -12 file1         : to print top 12 lines
tail file1             : to print bottom 10 lines

FIND A FILE:
================
find / -name meminfo   : to find a particular file in linux


